{{Infobox airport | name = Amasya Merzifon Airport | nativename = ''Amasya Merzifon Havalimanı'' | image = Amasya Merzifon Airport.jpg | image-width = 250 | IATA = MZH | ICAO = LTAP |pushpin_map= Turkey |pushpin_mapsize=200 |pushpin_mark=Airplane_silhouette.svg |pushpin_label=MZH | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Turkey | type = Public / Military | owner = | operator = General Directorate of State Airports Authority | city-served = | location = [[Merzifon]], [[Amasya Province|Amasya]], [[Turkey]] | elevation-f = 1,758 | elevation-m = 536 |coordinates = {{coord|40|49|45|N|035|31|19|E|display=inline,title}} | website = http://merzifon.dhmi.gov.tr/ | metric-rwy = Y | r1-number = 05/23 | r1-length-f = 9,600 | r1-length-m = 2,926 | r1-surface = Asphalt | footnotes = Source: [[DAFIF]]<ref name=WAD>{{WAD|LTAP|source=[[DAFIF]]}}</ref><ref name=GCM>{{GCM|LTAP|source=[[DAFIF]]}}</ref> }} [[File:AmasyaMerzifonAirport-June2016.jpg|thumb|Aeriak view of the airport.]]
'''Merzifon Airport''' or '''Amasya Merzifon Airport''' {{Airport codes|MZH|LTAP}} is a military [[airport]] located in the city of [[Merzifon]] in the [[Amasya Province]] of [[Turkey]].
==Airlines and destinations== {{airport-dest-list |[[Pegasus Airlines]] | [[Sabiha Gökçen International Airport|Istanbul–Sabiha Gökçen]] |[[Turkish Airlines]] | [[Istanbul–Atatürk]] (ends 31 December 2018),<ref name="move"/> [[Istanbul Airport|Istanbul–Havalimanı]] (begins 1 January 2019)<ref name="move">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ch-aviation.com/portal/news/71740-turkish-airlines-to-fully-move-to-istanbul-new-in-late-4q18|title=Turkish Airlines to fully move to Istanbul New in late 4Q18|date=16 October 2018|website=ch-aviation.com|access-date=2018-10-16}}</ref> }}
==Military usage== Merzifon is the 5th Air Wing (''Ana Jet Üs'' or ''AJÜ'') of the 2nd Air Force Command (''Hava Kuvvet Komutanligi'') of the [[Turkish Air Force]] (''Türk Hava Kuvvetleri''). Other wings of this command are located in [[Malatya]]/Erhaç (LTAT), [[Diyarbakır]] (LTCC) and [[İncirlik]] (LTAG).<ref>[http://www.scramble.nl/tr.htm scramble.nl - Turkish Air Force] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101001022410/http://www.scramble.nl/tr.htm |date=2010-10-01 }}</ref>
