The '''Balkan donkey''' or '''mountain donkey''', {{lang-sr|'''Domaći balkanski magarac'''}}, is a [[breed]] of domestic [[donkey]] originating in the [[Balkans]].<ref name=dad>[http://dad.fao.org/cgi-bin/EfabisWeb.cgi?sid=0b1613ebf16355cf65f6a05b9a65fe25,reportsreport8a_50000113 Breed data sheet: Balkan donkey / Serbia]. Domestic Animal Diversity Information System of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. Accessed May 2014.</ref> It is reported from [[Serbia]]<ref name=dad/> and [[Montenegro]].<ref name=dad2>[http://dad.fao.org/cgi-bin/EfabisWeb.cgi?sid=0b1613ebf16355cf65f6a05b9a65fe25,reportsreport8a_50014301 Breed data sheet: Balkanski magarac / Montenegro]. Domestic Animal Diversity Information System of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations. Accessed May 2014.</ref>

A herd of about 120 Balkan donkeys in the [[Zasavica (bog)|Zasavica Reserve]], [[Sremska Mitrovica]], [[Serbia]] are used to make the world's most expensive cheese, [[pule cheese]].<ref>[http://www.b92.net/eng/news/society-article.php?yyyy=2010&mm=03&dd=08&nav_id=65668 B92 - News - Balkan donkey, and "world's priciest cheese"<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>{{Citation | last = | first = | author = J.Slatinac| title = Svetski dan magaraca na Zasavici | newspaper = [[Politika]] | pages =  | language = Serbian | date = 1 May 2011| url = }}</ref>

