{{Infobox airport | name = Carnot Airport | nativename = ''Aéroport de Carnot'' | image = | IATA = CRF | ICAO = FEFC | type = Public | owner = Government | operator = | city-served = [[Carnot, Central African Republic]] | location = | elevation-f = 1985 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|4|56|20|N|15|53|37|E|type:airport|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Central African Republic | pushpin_label = '''CRF''' | pushpin_map_caption = Location of Carnot Airport in the Central African Republic | website = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 17/35 | r1-length-f = | r1-length-m = 1205 | r1-surface = Grass | footnotes = Source: Landings.com<ref name="Landings">[http://aerobaticsweb.org/cgi-bin/search_apt?FEFC Airport record for Carnot Airport] at Landings.com. Retrieved 2013-08-25</ref> Google Maps<ref name="Google">{{Google maps|url=https://maps.google.com/maps?ht=en&z=13&t=k&q=4.93805555555556,15.8938055555556+%28Carnot+Airport%29|title=location of Carnot Airport|accessdate=2013-08-25}}</ref> GCM<ref>{{GCM|CRF|Carnot Airport}}</ref> }}
'''Carnot Airport''' ({{lang-fr|Aéroport de Carnot}}) {{airport codes|CRF|FEFC}} is an [[airstrip]] serving [[Carnot, Central African Republic|Carnot]], a city in the [[Mambéré-Kadéï]] prefecture of the [[Central African Republic]]. The runway is on the western edge of the city.
The Berberati [[VHF omnidirectional range|VOR]] (Ident: '''BT''') is located {{convert|42.8|nmi|km|1}} south of the airstrip.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/BT/Berberati_VOR_CF/|title=Berberati VOR (BT) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
