{{other uses|Dvorce (disambiguation)}}

'''Dvorce''' is the name of a village in the [[Levoča]] district of [[Slovakia]]. After over 600 years, the village was evacuated and destroyed in the 1950s to make way for the [[Javorina]] military training area.<ref>[http://www.geocaching.sk/geocache-detail.php?id=506190 (Partially translated Slovak description and location information)]. Geocaching.sk. Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref> Former inhabitants light candles at the sight of their former homes, but must seek permission to do so.

Dvorce has been known by various names: Hungarian: Dvorecz (1869 place name<ref>[http://www.iabsi.com/gen/public/census_1869_fhl_holdings_by_magy.htm (The 1869 Hungarian Census index listed by Hungarian name)]. Iabsi.com. Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref><ref>[http://www.iabsi.com/gen/public/Census_1869_at_LDS.htm#1869village (The 1869 Census cross-reference Slovakia index files)]. Iabsi.com (2004-12-08). Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref>
<ref>[http://www.iabsi.com/gen/public/Documents/1869%20LDS%20census%20Slovak-ordered.pdf (the 1869 Hungarian Census index listed by Slovak name.)]. (PDF) . Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref>), now Szepesudvard (current usage) 

{{coord|49|05|N|20|34|E|display=title|region:SK_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}

<ref>[http://www.radixhub.com/radixhub/places/levoca_%5Bdvorce%5D#intro Places :: Levoča [Dvorce&#93;]. RadixHub. Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref><ref>[http://www.radixhub.com/radixhub/gazetteers/1913/szepes.htm#095380 Gazetteers :: The 1913 gazetteer of Hungary :: Szepes County]. RadixHub. Retrieved on 2011-09-24.</ref> and German Burgerhof.

Dvorce was part of the Szepes county of the kingdom of Hungary and was under the district of Levoča.

