{{one source|date=April 2014}} The '''Guinean Press Agency''' ({{lang-fr|Agence Guinéenne de Presse}}) ('''AGP''') is a press agency in [[Guinea]]. It was run by the government under [[Sékou Touré]] and provided daily news updates to the other government officials and international diplomatic corps.<ref>{{cite book|author1=O'Toole, Thomas |author2=Baker, Janice E. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kIiHwg3Y5u4C&pg=PA3&dq=Historical+dictionary+of+Guinea+Guinean+Press+Agency#v=onepage&q=&f=false|title=Historical Dictionary of Guinea|publisher=Volume 94 of African historical dictionaries, [[Scarecrow Press]]|year=2005|page=3|isbn=0-8108-4634-9}}</ref> A revitalized press emerged during the coup of April 1984. The agency is still active as of November 2015.
