{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2012}}
{{Use British English|date=December 2012}}
The '''Memorandum by Her Majesty's Government on the Report of the Constitution Committee''', or the '''Hattersley Memorandum''' for short (by [[Roy Hattersley]], Minister of State, [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]] of the United Kingdom), dated 26 June 1976, was the answer of the [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]] British Government to proposed constitutional changes in [[Gibraltar]] ruling out the possibility of integration of Gibraltar with the [[United Kingdom]].

In September 1975, [[Roy Hattersley]] (a Minister in the [[Foreign and Commonwealth Office]]) had visited Gibraltar and made it clear that the integration with the United Kingdom was not an option for Gibraltar.<ref name="Gold">{{cite book | first = Peter | last = Gold | title = Gibraltar: British or Spanish?  | url = https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=b6SgDQvP3zMC&lpg=PR6&dq=Gold%2C%20Peter%20(2005).%20Gibraltar%3A%20British%20or%20Spanish%3F.%20Routledge.%20p.%2022&pg=PA22#v=onepage&q&f=false | isbn = 0-415-34795-5 | pages = 22 | year = 2005 | publisher = Routledge}}</ref><ref name="Williams">{{cite book | first = William | last = Jackson | year = 1990 | title = The Rock of the Gibraltarians. A History of Gibraltar | publisher = Gibraltar Books | edition = 2nd | location = Grendon, Northamptonshire, UK | isbn = 0-948466-14-6 | pages = 323}}</ref>
However, during early 1976, a Gibraltarian inter-party Constitution Committee began to work on a proposal of constitutional changes that involved a further integration of Gibraltar with the United Kingdom. A delegation of the Constitution Committee visited [[London]] in June 1976, but were unable to convince the United Kingdom Government which, as response, issued a memorandum dated 26 June 1976 rejecting the proposals on the grounds of "avoid innovations which might result in prolongation of the frontier restrictions imposed by [[Spain]]".<ref>[http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/written_answers/1976/aug/03/gibraltar Written answer of Mr. Hattersley to Mrs. Hart], HC Deb 3 August 1976 vol 916 cc726-7W.</ref> The memorandum ruled out the option of integration of Gibraltar with the United Kingdom.

Apart for removing such an option from the constitutional and political development of Gibraltar, it effectively disbanded the [[Integration with Britain Party]], which had been in office from 1969 to 1972, and was the main supporter of the integration of Gibraltar into the United Kingdom.<ref name="Williams"/><ref>[http://www.foghs.org.uk/nl/68.pdf Obituary of former governor John Grandy], by [[Maurice Xiberras]]</ref>

