The '''High Council of Justice''' ({{lang-nl|Hoge Raad voor de Justitie}}, {{lang-fr|Conseil supérieur de la Justice}}, {{lang-de|Hohe Justizrat}}) plays a central role in the [[Judiciary of Belgium|judicial system of]] [[Belgium]]. It was established in 1999 by Article 151 of the [[Constitution of Belgium|Belgian Constitution]] and is responsible for exercising external oversight over the operation of the judicial system, handling complaints, submitting advice and opinions to policymakers, nominating candidates for appointments to the judiciary and preparing guidelines for the training of the members of the [[Magistrate#Continental Europe and its former colonies|magistracy]]. == See also == *[[List of Belgian Judges]] ==External links== * [http://www.hrj.be/ Website of the High Council of Justice]
