'''The International Academy of Mathematical Chemistry''' (IAMC) was founded in [[Dubrovnik]] ([[Croatia]]) in 2005 by [[Milan Randić]].<ref name="iamc"/> It is an organization for chemistry and mathematics avocation, and its predecessors have been around since the 1930s.<ref name="iamc"/> The Academy Members are 88 (2011) from all over the world (27 countries), comprising six scientists awarded the [[Nobel Prize]].<ref name="iamc">[http://www.iamc-online.org/ IAMC Home page]</ref>
