{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Use British English|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox street | name =Signal Station Road | native_name = | image =Signal Station 3.jpg | caption =Signal Station Road and station | former_names = | postal_code = | addresses = | length_km = | length_round = | width = | location =[[Gibraltar]] | client = | owner =[[Government of Gibraltar]] | current_tenants = | sector = | category = | coordinates =<!-- {{Coord|36.139682|-5.353794|region:GI_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | commissioning_date = | construction_start_date = | completion_date = | inauguration_date = | demolition_date = | main_contractor = | cost = }} '''Signal Station Road''' is a road in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. It leads down from the top of the [[Rock of Gibraltar]],<ref name="BrownBaskett2009">{{cite book|last1=Brown|first1=Jules|last2=Baskett|first2=Simon|last3=Garvey|first3=Geoff|title=The Rough Guide to Spain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Fjyv9lYSoGgC&pg=PT627|accessdate=2 May 2013|date=1 April 2009|publisher=Rough Guides Limited|isbn=978-1-84836-837-8|page=627}}</ref> and skirts the [[Upper Rock Nature Reserve]].
==Description== [[File:Gibraltar MOD warning signs.jpg|thumb|left|MOD multilingual warning signs on fencing along the road in [[English language|English]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Arabic languages|Arabic]], those being some of the main [[languages of Gibraltar]]]]
The road takes its name from an old [[Signal Hill Battery, Gibraltar|signal station]] built by the British on the clifftop. A footpath known as either Green's Lodge Road or Green's Lodge footpath leads out through a break in the (former) high-voltage fencing on one side of the road. This footpath leads to [[Green's Lodge Battery]].<ref name=trail>{{cite web|last=Crone|first=Jim|title=Green's Lodge Battery - Nature Trail|url=http://www.discovergibraltar.com/pages/mainlogo/mainfrm.htm|publisher=DiscoverGibraltar.com|accessdate=6 May 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130905140025/http://www.discovergibraltar.com/pages/mainlogo/mainfrm.htm|archivedate=5 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The boundary fencing still has signs in [[English language|English]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]] and [[Arabic languages|Arabic]] warning people of the high-voltage fencing and not to enter the restricted Ministry of Defence area. Actually the land was given to the [[Gibraltar Ornithological and Natural History Society]] in 2005 and is not restricted or the fence electrified, although the area at the top of the rock which carries radio antennae is still restricted.<ref name=trail/>
[[Governor's Lookout Battery]] is located along the road and the battery's name is because this is thought to be where the defence was directed during the [[Great Siege of Gibraltar]]. It is now the location of [[Scouting and Guiding in Gibraltar|Gibraltar's scouts camp]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Scouts|url=http://www.gibscouts.com/scouts.html|publisher=[[Scouting and Guiding in Gibraltar|Gibraltar Scouts Association]]|accessdate=24 March 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711093040/http://www.gibscouts.com/scouts.html|archivedate=11 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>
